                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#163ra">Fol. 163ra</locus>: Incipit of Text I-12.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written probably in the same hand as that of Additio 2 (the same hand as that of the main text?) by mistake or as a writing excercise (?).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#173ra">Fol. 173ra</locus>: Inventory of the books and items of ʾAḥzara Maryam.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 173ra: ኍልቈ፡ መጻሕፍት፡ ዘአህዘሬ፡ ፪ወንጌል፡ ፩ግብረ፡ ሕማማት፡ ፪ሰንክሳር፡ ፬ተአምር፡ ፪ተአምረ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ፩ሳዊሮስ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The inventory seems to have been written in two different hands (the same hand as that of the main text and that of Additio 1). The name of the church is spelled ʾAḥzare. An addition has been made in blue pen.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#176r">Fol. 176r</locus>: Record concerning reconciliation.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in Amharic. The note is about reconciliation and assignation of land.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omissions or corrections are written interlineally in fols. 41ra, 53rc, 63va, 101va, 158va.&#xD;
- Blank space for text dividers (?) left unfilled in fols. 105va, 131va, 147va.</item>
                     </list>
